    <briefdescription>
<para>Tee parameter. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="structtee__param_1ac8ced719ce993735e22d68ca50f54e5b" kindref="member">attr</ref> &amp; TEE_PARAM_ATTR_TYPE_MASK indicates if memref or value is used in the union. TEE_PARAM_ATTR_TYPE_VALUE_* indicates value and TEE_PARAM_ATTR_TYPE_MEMREF_* indicates memref. TEE_PARAM_ATTR_TYPE_NONE indicates that none of the members are used.</para>
<para>Shared memory is allocated with TEE_IOC_SHM_ALLOC which returns an identifier representing the shared memory object. A memref can reference a part of a shared memory by specifying an offset (<ref refid="structtee__param_1aea8916d1bc24ab5a56f59fa4608f1a38" kindref="member">a</ref>) and size (<ref refid="structtee__param_1a22785fe00950c3a7d6353c39b12d72a8" kindref="member">b</ref>) of the object. To supply the entire shared memory object set the offset (<ref refid="structtee__param_1aea8916d1bc24ab5a56f59fa4608f1a38" kindref="member">a</ref>) to 0 and size (<ref refid="structtee__param_1a22785fe00950c3a7d6353c39b12d72a8" kindref="member">b</ref>) to the previously returned size of the object. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
